What is the difference between an Interface and Abstract class?
A.abstract class contain at least one abstract method but the methods in the interface are all abstract (without implementation)
interface use implements key word and abstract class use extends
variables in interface are all final but in abstract class not
all methods and variables are public in the interface but int abstract class they can be modified
Can you make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class ? if not how do you use it ?
A. no we cannot. in order to use them we have to assign them to the classes that implements the interface or use the inherited class
what is Access Specifier?
A. access specifier is a key word used to determine the access to a method or variable (public protected private default)
What is OOP ? Define each feature of java OOP.
object oriented programming
1- abstraction :used with interface and abstract class
2- polymorphism: concept of overriding and overloading
3-encapsulation: data hiding
4- inheritance: class inherit from an other class

